frameDefinitions: An Item becomes filled with a Substance as a result of movement of liquid into visible or invisible interstices in the Item.
An Agent performs an Action incorrectly.
An Entity undergoes some change (the Event) that is (or is construed as) punctual.

This frame models the semantic contribution of negation, in which the profiled content of the Negated_proposition is asserted to contrast incompatibly with a corresponding Factual_situation, which is normally implicit.
The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.
The words in this frame describe acts (or situations characterized by acts) that cause injury or harm.
frameExamples: Paper and board <t>absorb</t> moisture in the winter.
This <t>happens</t> to me all the time.
The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
Research on whether concealed carry laws increase gun <t>violence</t> among gang members has been inconclusive.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Item</fen> is the absorbant friendly thing that takes in the <fen>Substance</fen>.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the material that is taken in by the <fen>Item</fen>.
When the <fen>Item</fen> takes in <fen>Substance</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Item</fen> takes in <fen>Substance</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> performs an action incorrectly.
<fen>Patient</fen> is the entity affected by the <fen>Agent</fen>'s bungling of an <fen>Action</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Action</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs incorrectly.
The type of action that the <fen>Agent</fen> habitually bungles.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the bungling occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the bungling occurs.
This role identifies the event which occurs and affects the <fen>Entity</fen>.
This role identifies the entity, concrete or abstract.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
This role identifies where the event takes place.
The situation which is presented as false overall. The particular focus of negation which contrasts with the <fen>Factual_situation</fen> is not separately marked.

The situation or part of situation that actually pertains, in contradistinction to the profiled situation in the <fen>Negated_proposition</fen> that is asserted not to pertain.  In spoken language and casual written language, but not in normatively edited written texts, the <fen>Factual_situation</fen> may be expressed as an unmarked clause immediately preceding or following the <fen>Negated_proposition</fen>.
The undesirable event which occurs.
The entity that experiences the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen>.
When the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> takes place.
The <fen>Aggressor</fen> is the person causing the <fen>Victim</fen>'s injury.
The <fen>Victim</fen> is the being or entity that is injured.
The <fen>Cause</fen> marks expressions that indicate some non-intentional, typically non-human, force that inflicts harm on the <fen>Victim</fen>
The <fen>Aggressors</fen> commit acts of violence upon each other.
<fen>Time</fen> identifies the time when the harm-causing event occurs.
<fen>Place</fen> identifies the place where the violence occurs.

She did n't know, <fex>rather she suspected</fex> .
An <fex>environmental</fex> disaster is just what we need.
<fex>Your</fex> brutality on your enemies seems to know no boundaries.
Increasing violence against supporters of government reform have attracted international attention.
<fex>The storm's</fex> violence left many lives in shambles.
Hope for a peaceful resoliton is gone as violence <fex>between the two sides</fex> reignites.
<fex>Last week's</fex> violence resulted in over three hundred injuries.
City leaders are troubled by recent surges in <fex>local</fex> violence
